lyrics:
(Verse)
Scrimmy Bradshaw, with a tale so grand,
Married into a land of promised sand.
Calls his in-laws “JooLaws,” with a laugh,
A mix of cultures, his better half.

(Chorus)
Scrimmy and the JooLaws, oh what a sight,
Football Sundays and Hanukkah lights.
In this family, love knows no bounds,
Where laughter and joy always resounds.
